'''Thibaut Nicolas Marc Courtois''' ({{IPA|fr|tibo kuʁtwa}}; {{IPA|nl|ˈtiboː kurˈtʋaː}}; born 11 May 1992) is a Belgian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Spanish football updater|Real Madrid}} club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]]. Regarded as one of the greatest goalkeepers of all time,<ref>{{cite news |date=24 January 2025 |title=Ranking the 15 greatest goalkeepers in football history |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/ranking-the-15-greatest-goalkeepers-in-football-history-38974080 |access-date=24 January 2025 |website=OneFootball}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Murray |first=Will |date=15 April 2020 |title=Ranking the 20 Greatest Goalkeepers in Football History |url=https://www.givemesport.com/football-soccer-best-goalkeepers-history/ |access-date=24 January 2025 |website=GiveMeSport}}</ref><ref name="Best Soccer Goalkeepers">{{cite web |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/best-soccer-goalkeepers-of-all-time |title=Best Soccer Goalkeepers of All Time |publisher=Sports Illustrated |first=Amanda |last= Langell |date=19 November 2024 |access-date=24 January 2025 }}</ref> he is known for his reflexes, acrobatic saves, and command of the penalty area.<ref>{{cite web |date=7 May 2021 |title=Ranked! The 10 best goalkeepers in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/ranked-the-10-best-goalkeepers-in-the-world |access-date=1 September 2021 |website=FourFourTwo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=1 September 2021 |title=The 10 Best Goalkeepers In The World Right Now, Named And Ranked |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/best-goalkeepers-right-now-20210820 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231006203020/https://www.sportbible.com/football/best-goalkeepers-right-now-20210820 |archive-date=6 October 2023 |access-date=1 September 2021 |website=SPORTbible}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Thibaut Courtois wins FIFA's 'The Best' Goalkeeper award |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/thibaut-courtois-wins-fifa-s-the-best-goalkeeper-award-508194 |access-date=1 September 2021 |website=BeSoccer}}</ref>

Courtois began his career with [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] and made his senior debut in 2009, at age 16; he went on to establish himself as the club's starting goalkeeper and won the [[2010–11 Belgian Pro League|Belgian Pro League]]. In 2011, Courtois signed for [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] in a transfer worth a reported £8&nbsp;million (€9 million), but then joined [[Atlético Madrid]] on loan. At Atlético, Courtois won a [[2013–14 La Liga|La Liga]] title, the [[2012–13 Copa del Rey|Copa del Rey]], the [[2011–12 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]], and reached the [[2013–14 UEFA Champions League|UEFA Champions League final]]. He returned to Chelsea in 2014 and won two [[Premier League]] titles and the [[2014–15 Football League Cup|EFL Cup]]. In 2018, Courtois signed for Real Madrid in a deal worth a reported £35&nbsp;million (€38.8&nbsp;million), becoming La Liga's most expensive goalkeeper, and where he has gone on to win three La Liga and two [[UEFA Champions League]] titles.

Courtois made his senior international debut for Belgium in 2011 at age 19, becoming their youngest senior international goalkeeper. He has since earned over 100 caps, ranking [[Belgium national football team records and statistics#General|eighth-highest]] for appearances, while 
appearing in five major tournaments. At the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], Courtois won the [[FIFA World Cup awards#Golden Glove|Golden Glove]] as the best goalkeeper as he helped Belgium finish third, their highest-ever finish at the competition.

Courtois has won the [[Ricardo Zamora Trophy]] three times, the [[Premier League Golden Glove]] once, and was named the [[IFFHS World's Best Goalkeeper#The World's Best Man Goalkeeper of the Decade (2011–2020)|third-best goalkeeper]] of the decade (2011–2020) by the [[International Federation of Football History & Statistics]] (IFFHS).

==Club career==
===Early career at Genk===
[[File:Thibaut Courtois.jpg|thumb|left|upright|Courtois with [[KRC Genk|Genk]] during the 2010–11 season]]

Courtois was born in the city of [[Bree, Belgium|Bree]] in [[Flanders]], to a [[Walloons|Walloon]] father and a [[Flemings|Flemish]] mother.<ref name="theguardian1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2012/aug/30/thibaut-courtois-atletico-madrid-chelsea|title = All right on the night for Atlético Madrid's Chelsea-owned keeper|website = [[TheGuardian.com]]|date = 30 August 2012}}</ref> He began his career with local side Bilzen V.V.,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kbilzersevv.be/ |title=K.Bilzerse-Waltwilder VV |website=kbilzersevv.be |access-date=20 August 2011 |archive-date=31 March 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120331000001/http://www.kbilzersevv.be/ |url-status=dead }}</ref> as a [[left back]]. Soon after, in 1999, he joined [[Racing Genk]] at the age of seven, and it was there that he was converted into a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]].

Courtois progressed through the [[KRC Genk|Genk]] youth system, where [[Koen Casteels]] was initially regarded as the primary goalkeeper, but during an injury crisis Courtois, aged 16 years and 341 days, made his first team debut on 17 April 2009 against [[KAA Gent|Gent]]. After turning down a transfer to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim]] of the [[Bundesliga]], Courtois was made first-choice goalkeeper for the 2010–11 season ahead of Casteels, when [[Laszlo Koteles]]' registration ran into issues.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Terreur |first1=Kristof |title=Chelsea's Thibaut Courtois: from clumsy boy to top of the world |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/sep/20/chelsea-thibaut-courtois-profile |access-date=12 July 2018 |newspaper=The Observer |date=20 September 2014}}</ref>

He was a key figure in Genk's title victory in the [[2010–11 Belgian Pro League|2010–11 season in the Belgian Pro League]]. He received the Goalkeeper of the Year and Genk's Player of the Year award, only conceding 32 goals over the course of 40 league matches and keeping 14 [[clean sheet]]s for Genk.<ref>{{cite web |title=Courtois History |url=http://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/video-evidence-thibaut-courtois-genks-19-year-old-goalie-who-chelsea-man-united-spurs-newcastle-all-want/ |publisher=101 Great Goals |access-date=28 June 2014 |archive-date=29 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190529204713/https://www.101greatgoals.com/blog/video-evidence-thibaut-courtois-genks-19-year-old-goalie-who-chelsea-man-united-spurs-newcastle-all-want/ |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://hosted.stats.com/belg/players.asp?player=90824 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120406062606/http://hosted.stats.com/belg/players.asp?player=90824 |archive-date=6 April 2012 |title=STATS Hosted Solution &#124; Player Stats – Thibaut Courtois – Racing Genk |publisher=Hosted.stats.com |access-date=27 April 2012}}</ref>

===Atlético Madrid===
In July 2011, Courtois joined [[Premier League]] club [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] for a reported €9&nbsp;million, signing a five-year deal.<ref name="chelseasigning">{{cite web |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/2402319|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130804060836/http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/2402319|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 August 2013 |title=Courtois Completed |date=26 July 2011 |publisher=[[Chelsea F.C.]] |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2011/jul/16/chelsea-thibaut-courtois-genk-goalkeeper |title=Chelsea agree deal to sign goalkeeper Thibaut Courtois from Genk |newspaper=The Guardian |date=16 July 2011 |access-date=20 November 2015}}</ref> Within weeks of joining Chelsea, Courtois was sent on a season-long loan to [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Courtois on Loan |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/1791236|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140628102629/http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/1791236|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 June 2014 |publisher=[[Chelsea F.C.]] |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref>

====2011–12 season====
Courtois made his debut for Atlético in a 4–0 [[2011–12 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] victory over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] on 25 August,<ref>{{cite web |title=Match: Guimaraes v Atlético Madrid – Europa League |url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/statistics/id/327646/statistics.html |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref> and three days later kept a clean sheet on his La Liga debut, a goalless draw against [[CA Osasuna|Osasuna]] at the [[Vicente Calderón Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lineras |first1=Ángel |title=El Atlético añora un delantero de referencia|trans-title=Atlético yearn for an established forward |url=http://www.marca.com/marcador/futbol/2011_12/primera/jornada_2/atm_osa/ |access-date=11 April 2015 |newspaper=Marca |location=Spain |date=28 August 2011 |language=es}}</ref> Courtois became first-choice goalkeeper over [[Sergio Asenjo]], keeping four clean sheets in his first six La Liga games.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/player/134283/thibaut-courtois?season=2011 |title=Thibaut Courtois Bio, Stats, News – Football / Soccer – – ESPN Soccernet |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/324015/gamecast.html |title=Match: Atlético Madrid v Osasuna – Spanish Primera División – ESPN Soccernet |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |date=28 August 2011 |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/323997/gamecast.html |title=Match: Atlético Madrid v Racing Santander – Spanish Primera División – ESPN Soccernet |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |date=18 September 2011 |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/323993/gamecast.html |title=Match: Atlético Madrid v Sporting Gijon – Spanish Primera División – ESPN Soccernet |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |date=21 September 2011 |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/323975/gamecast.html |title=Match: Atlético Madrid v Sevilla FC – Spanish Primera División – ESPN Soccernet |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |date=2 October 2011 |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref> On 26 November 2011, Courtois received his first red card of his professional career after fouling [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]]'s [[Karim Benzema]] for a penalty in the [[El Derbi madrileño|Madrid derby]]. [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] put the penalty past substitute goalkeeper Asenjo as Atlético lost 1–4.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lowe |first1=Sid |title=Cristiano Ronaldo bookends Real Madrid's comeback win against Atlético |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2011/nov/26/real-madrid-atletico-madrid-la-liga |access-date=11 April 2015 |newspaper=The Guardian |date=26 November 2011}}</ref> Atlético reached the [[2012 UEFA Europa League final]], and Courtois kept a clean sheet as the club won 3–0 over fellow Spanish side [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Report: Atlético Madrid vs Athletic Bilbao |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=341106&cc=5901 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120512060222/http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=341106&cc=5901 |archive-date=12 May 2012 |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |access-date=11 May 2012}}</ref>

====2012–13 season====
[[File:Thibaut Courtois - 02.jpg|thumb|upright|Courtois playing for Atlético Madrid in 2013]]

Courtois' loan to Atlético was extended to cover the [[2012–13 Atlético Madrid season|2012–13 season]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Courtois to stay in Spain |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/2832263|archive-url=https://archive.today/20140628102524/http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/2832263|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 June 2014 |publisher=[[Chelsea F.C.]] |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref> His first game of the loan extension was against parent club Chelsea in the [[2012 UEFA Super Cup]] in [[Monaco]], which ended in a 4–1 victory for Atlético Madrid. Later in the season Courtois set a new Atlético Madrid record of 820 minutes without conceding a goal at the [[Estadio Vicente Calderon]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://espnfc.com/news/story/_/id/1371702/courtois-hopeful-atleti-extension?cc=5901 |title=Courtois hopeful of Atleti extension |publisher=[[ESPN FC]] |date=12 March 2013}}</ref> ended by being beaten in a 1–0 loss to [[Real Sociedad]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asia.eurosport.com/football/la-liga/2011-2012/atletico-madrid-v-real-sociedad-live_sto3660237/story.shtml |title=Prieto strikes as Sociedad stun Atletico |publisher=[[Eurosport]] |date=11 March 2013 |access-date=12 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004024443/http://asia.eurosport.com/football/la-liga/2011-2012/atletico-madrid-v-real-sociedad-live_sto3660237/story.shtml |archive-date=4 October 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Atlético reached the [[2013 Copa del Rey Final]], and Courtois was named [[man of the match]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/apr/12/atletico-madrid-thibaut-courtois-chelsea |title=Atlético Madrid's Thibaut Courtois could be thorn in Chelsea's side |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |first=Paul |last=Doyle |date=12 April 2014 |access-date=2 May 2014}}</ref> in a 2–1 victory against Real, the first time that Atlético had beaten their city rivals in 14 years.

====2013–14 season====
For the [[2013–14 Atlético Madrid season|2013–14 season]], Courtois' loan to Atlético was extended by a further 12 months.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/3219030/title/courtois-loan-extended |title=Courtois loan extended |publisher=[[Chelsea F.C.]] |date=24 June 2013 |access-date=24 June 2013 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140108153228/http://www.chelseafc.com/news-article/article/3219030/title/courtois-loan-extended |archive-date=8 January 2014}}</ref>

When Atlético were drawn to play Chelsea in the [[2013–14 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Semi-finals|Champions League semi-final]], it was reported that a clause in Courtois' contract required Atlético to pay Chelsea €3&nbsp;million per match if they selected him against his parent club, and that Atlético could not afford such a sum. UEFA made it clear that considerations of sporting integrity made such a clause "null, void and unenforceable", and confirmed that Atlético were free to select Courtois without making any such payment.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://as.com/diarioas/2014/04/10/english/1397147582_658656.html |title=Atlético have to pay to play Courtois if they draw Chelsea |first=Dani |last=Hidalgo |newspaper=Diario AS |date=10 April 2014 |access-date=15 May 2014 |archive-date=17 May 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140517120113/http://as.com/diarioas/2014/04/10/english/1397147582_658656.html |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/26972498 |title=Chelsea: Atletico keeper Thibaut Courtois cleared to play in semi |website=[[BBC Sport]] |date=10 April 2014 |access-date=15 May 2014}}</ref>

By conceding the fewest goals in a substantial number of matches during the 2013–14 season, Courtois won the [[Ricardo Zamora Trophy]] and made an important contribution to Atlético's 2013–14 La Liga title, their first since 1996. He was nominated for the La Liga Award for the best goalkeeper in the league, alongside [[Willy Caballero]] of [[Málaga CF|Málaga]] and [[Keylor Navas]] of [[Levante UD|Levante]], which Navas eventually won.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fernandez-Abascal |first1=Eduardo |title=Chelsea Duo Thibaut Courtois And Filipe Luis Nominated For La Liga Awards |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.uk/chelsea-duo-thibaut-courtois-filipe-luis-nominated-la-liga-awards-1470026 |access-date=15 October 2014 |newspaper=International Business Times |date=14 October 2014}}</ref> Atlético, however, lost the [[2014 UEFA Champions League final|UEFA Champions League final]] 4–1 [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|after extra time]] against neighbours Real Madrid on 24 May in Lisbon.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2011883--real-madrid-vs-atleti/ |title=Real Madrid 4–1 Atlético |publisher=UEFA |date=24 May 2014 |access-date=2 July 2018}}</ref>

===Chelsea===
====2014–15 season====
[[File:Chelsea 2 QPR 1 (15066336874).jpg|thumb|upright|Courtois playing for Chelsea in 2014]]

In June 2014, Chelsea manager [[José Mourinho]] confirmed that Courtois would return to Chelsea for the upcoming season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Thibaut Courtois: Jose Mourinho says keeper will return to Chelsea And would be the future of Chelsea fc |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27857265 |access-date=18 June 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=16 June 2014}}</ref> He was assigned the number 13 shirt, last worn by [[Victor Moses]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Squad number changes |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2014/08/squad-number-changes.html?WT.mc_id=social_20140815_29820286 |publisher=[[Chelsea F.C.]] |access-date=15 August 2014}}</ref> On 18 August, Mourinho announced that Courtois would start the Premier League opener against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] in place of [[Petr Čech]]. Although he conceded the first goal to [[Scott Arfield]] at [[Turf Moor]], Chelsea won 3–1.<ref>{{cite news |title=Burnley 1–3 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/28735901 |access-date=18 August 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=18 August 2014}}</ref> Courtois kept his first Premier League clean sheet in his second game, making several crucial saves in a 2–0 home win over [[Leicester City]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ronay |first1=Barney |title=Diego Costa saves profligate Chelsea's blushes against Leicester City |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/aug/23/chelsea-leicester-premier-league-match-report |access-date=23 August 2014 |newspaper=The Guardian |date=23 August 2014}}</ref>

On 11 September 2014, Courtois signed a new five-year contract with Chelsea, keeping him at the club until 2019. Upon signing, Courtois said: "It’s really nice to have signed this new contract for five years."<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2014/09/courtois-signs-new-deal.html?WT.mc_id=social_20140911_31427856 |title=Courtois signs new deal |date=11 September 2014 |access-date=11 September 2014 |publisher=Chelsea F.C.}}</ref>

Courtois suffered a head injury in the first half of Chelsea's 2–0 home win over [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 5 October due to a collision with [[Alexis Sánchez]]; he was substituted and then taken to hospital.<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=Chelsea 2–0 Arsenal |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/29398780 |access-date=5 October 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=5 October 2014}}</ref> He was treated for a minor cut to his ear and released from hospital that night.<ref>{{cite news |title=Courtois update |url=http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2014/Oct%2014/courtois-update.html |access-date=6 October 2014 |publisher=[[Chelsea F.C.]] |date=6 October 2014 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008061916/http://www.chelseafc.com/news/latest-news/2014/Oct%2014/courtois-update.html |archive-date=8 October 2014}}</ref>

He won his first trophy with Chelsea on 1 March 2015, as they defeated [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] 2–0 in the [[2015 Football League Cup final|League Cup final]], with Čech instead playing in that match;<ref>{{cite news |last1=McNulty |first1=Phil |title=Chelsea 2–0 Tottenham |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31572594 |access-date=2 March 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=1 March 2015}}</ref> Chelsea also finished the season as league champions.

====2015–16 season====
[[File:2015 CHE PSG DSC02646 (16172587913).jpg|thumb|upright|Courtois playing for Chelsea in 2015]]

Courtois opened the season by playing in the [[2015 FA Community Shield]] on 2 August, a 1–0 loss to Arsenal.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cryer |first1=Andy |title=Arsenal 1–0 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33667216 |access-date=2 August 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=2 August 2015}}</ref> Six days later, as the Premier League campaign opened with a home fixture against [[Swansea City]], he was given a straight red card for conceding a penalty with a foul on [[Bafétimbi Gomis]], who converted the penalty past replacement [[Asmir Begović]] for a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Johnston |first1=Neil |title=Chelsea 2–2 Swansea |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33744668 |access-date=8 August 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=8 August 2015}}</ref> On his return on 23 August, Courtois saved a penalty from [[James Morrison (footballer)|James Morrison]] in a 3–2 win at [[West Bromwich Albion]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Magowan |first1=Alistair |title=West Brom 2–3 Chelsea |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/33950789 |access-date=23 August 2015 |website=BBC Sport |date=23 August 2015}}</ref> Courtois suffered a leg injury in training on 11 September which required surgery and meant that he was expected to miss the next three months of competition.<ref>{{cite news |title=Chelsea's Thibaut Courtois could be out until December with knee injury |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/sep/11/chelsea-thibaut-courtois-injury |newspaper=The Guardian |date=11 September 2015}}</ref>

On 16 April, he was sent off at home to [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] for conceding a penalty with a foul on [[Fernandinho (footballer, born May 1985)|Fernandinho]]; [[Sergio Agüero]] converted it past Begović to seal a 3–0 win. He became the sixth Premier League goalkeeper to be sent off twice in the same season.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reddy |first1=Luke |title=Chelsea 0–3 Manchester City |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36003978 |access-date=16 April 2016 |website=BBC Sport |date=16 April 2016}}</ref>

====2016–17 season====
On 17 August 2016, Courtois dismissed any transfer rumours and stated he would stay at Chelsea for many years to come.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espnfc.com/report?gameId=451007 |title=Diego Costa's late winner helps Chelsea defeat West Ham in opener |date=15 August 2016 |publisher=ESPN}}</ref> Ten days later in the 3–0 home victory over [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], Courtois kept the first clean sheet of the season and broke a run of thirteen home Premier League games without a clean sheet since November 2015.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/37139886 |title=Chelsea 3–0 Burnley |date=27 August 2016 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> From 1 October to 20 November, Chelsea earned a run of six games without conceding a single goal; with Courtois playing in all six of them.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/nov/20/antonio-conte-hails-sixth-successive-clean-sheet-chelsea |title=Antonio Conte hails sixth successive clean sheet for Chelsea |last=Taylor |first=Louise |date=20 November 2016 |website=The Guardian|access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.caughtoffside.com/2016/11/21/photo-chelsea-keeper-thanks-travelling-fans-after-keeping-6th-consecutive-clean-sheet/ |title=Chelsea keeper thanks travelling fans after keeping 6th consecutive clean sheet |date=21 November 2016 |website=CaughtOffside |access-date=8 July 2018 |language=en-US}}</ref> From 11 to 26 December, Courtois kept four clean sheets, as Chelsea were at the top of table in time for Christmas.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/38272816 |title=Crystal Palace 0–1 Chelsea |date=17 December 2016 |website=BBC Sport|access-date=8 July 2018 |language=en-GB}}</ref>

In April 2017, Courtois was ruled out for the match against rivals [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], as a result of suffering a reported ankle injury, which he sustained in training.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/chelsea/story/3105086/chelsea-goalkeeper-thibaut-courtois-to-miss-man-united-game-reports |title=Courtois to miss Man United game – reports |publisher=ESPN|access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref> Chelsea would go on to lose the match 0–2.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39543146 |title=Manchester United 2–0 Chelsea |date=16 April 2017 |website=BBC Sport|access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref> On 12 May 2017, Courtois kept his third consecutive clean sheet in a 1–0 away win over West Bromwich Albion, in which Chelsea secured the title.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39813798 |title=West Bromwich Albion 0–1 Chelsea |date=12 May 2017 |website=BBC Sport|access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref> Courtois also played for Chelsea in the [[2017 FA Cup final|FA Cup final]]; which Chelsea lost 2–1 to Arsenal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.thefa.com/news/2017/may/27/arsenal-chelsea-emirates-fa-cup-final-report-270517 |title=Arsenal 2–1 Chelsea |publisher=The Football Association |access-date=8 July 2018}}</ref>

Courtois kept a total of 16 clean sheets in the Premier League and won the [[Premier League Golden Glove|Golden Glove]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/players/clean_sheet |title=Premier League Player Stats – Clean sheets |publisher=Premier League |access-date=7 July 2018 |archive-date=19 June 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619142908/https://www.premierleague.com/stats/top/players/clean_sheet |url-status=dead }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
====2018–2020 ====
[[File:FC RB Salzburg versus Real Madrid (Testspiel, 7. August 2019) 03.jpg|thumb|upright|Courtois playing for Real Madrid in 2019]]

Following the 2017–18 season, Courtois mentioned he would want to live closer to his children, reigniting the rumours about a transfer to Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/chelsea-fc-transfer-rumours-news/2018/6/30/17519856/courtois-talks-children-and-madrid-as-transfer-rumors-catch-fire-again |title=Courtois talks children and Madrid as transfer rumors catch fire, again |website=weaintgotnohistory.com|date=30 June 2018 |access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/courtois-keeping-chelsea-real-madrid-guessing-but-admits-to/krh0qyg2sww41khrdbvwcp23jChelsea |title=Courtois keeping Chelsea & Real Madrid guessing but admits to future 'preference' |website=goal.com|access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref> After a strong performance at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], where he won the Golden Glove for best goalkeeper, Courtois expressed his interest in moving on.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/thibaut-courtois-refuses-rule-out-12844770 |title=Thibaut Courtois refuses to rule out Chelsea exit as keeper bids to win World Cup 2018 with Belgium |website=Mirror|date=3 July 2018 |access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sport.net/thibaut-courtois-throws-chelsea-into-turmoil-by-refusing-to-commit_732188 |title=Thibaut Courtois throws Chelsea into turmoil by refusing to commit |website=sport.net |access-date=9 August 2018 |archive-date=9 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180809184300/http://www.sport.net/thibaut-courtois-throws-chelsea-into-turmoil-by-refusing-to-commit_732188 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Chelsea stated they would not let him go unless they were able to find a replacement for him.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/real-madrid-waiting-for-chelsea-to-find-courtois-replacement/1koct8jmpshko15qm46zdow84n |title=Real Madrid waiting for Chelsea to find Courtois replacement |website=Goal.com|access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref> Courtois responded by not showing up for training after the summer break, trying to force his exit from Chelsea.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/08/06/exclusive-thibaut-courtois-attempts-force-chelsea-exit-going/ |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2018/08/06/exclusive-thibaut-courtois-attempts-force-chelsea-exit-going/ |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Exclusive: Thibaut Courtois attempts to force Chelsea exit by going AWOL ahead of new season |newspaper=The Telegraph|date=6 August 2018 |access-date=9 August 2018|last1=Law |first1=Matt }}{{cbignore}}</ref> On 8 August 2018, Real Madrid announced that they had signed Courtois on a six-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2018/08/official-announcement-thibaut-courtois |title=Official announcement: Thibaut Courtois |publisher=Real Madrid C.F.|access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref> A day later, Chelsea confirmed the transfer for a fee believed to be £35 million.<ref>{{Cite web |date=8 August 2018 |title=Chelsea reach deal to sell Courtois to Real Madrid |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/soccer-transfers/story/3589615/chelsea-and-real-madrid-agree-fee-for-transfer-of-goalkeeper-thibaut-courtois |access-date=28 May 2022 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.chelseafc.com/en/news/2018/8/9/courtois-departs |title=Courtois Departs |publisher=Chelsea F.C. |access-date=9 August 2018}}</ref>

He made his debut for Madrid on 1 September 2018, where he started in a 4–1 win over [[CD Leganés|Leganés]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2018/09/01/5b8afb20e2704e1cbf8b4586.html |title=Real Madrid rocket past Leganes |website=Marca|date=September 2018 |location=Spain|access-date=1 September 2018}}</ref>

On 12 January 2020, Real Madrid beat Courtois' former club [[Atlético Madrid]] in a penalty shootout to win their eleventh [[Supercopa de España]] title.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51085601|title=Spanish Super Cup: Real Madrid beat Atletico Madrid on penalties|date=12 January 2020|website=BBC Sport|access-date=9 February 2020|language=en-GB}}</ref> In the shootout, [[Saul Niguez|Saul]] saw his spot-kick hit the post before [[Thomas Partey|Thomas]]' effort was saved by Courtois, giving [[Sergio Ramos|Ramos]] the chance to secure Real's 11th Spanish Super Cup triumph.

On 5 July 2020, Courtois kept his 17th clean sheet of the [[2019–20 La Liga]] season in a 1–0 away win over Athletic Bilbao, becoming the first Real Madrid goalkeeper to do so in a single season since [[Francisco Buyo]] in [[1994–95 La Liga|1994–95]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/53298188 |title=Athletic Bilbao 0–1 Real Madrid: Sergio Ramos sends Real closer to title |website=BBC Sport |date=5 July 2020 |access-date=5 July 2020 }}</ref> He was the undisputed starter during the league season, as Real Madrid won the La Liga,<ref name="marca.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2020/07/17/5f10db2146163f3c2c8b45d7.html|title=Real Madrid win the longest LaLiga Santander season|date=17 July 2020|access-date=17 July 2020|website=Marca|location=Spain}}</ref> becoming the first player since [[José Luis Pérez-Payá]] in [[1953–54 La Liga|1954]] to be crowned champion with both Real Madrid and Atlético Madrid.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/real-madrid/2020/07/18/5f1227e922601d187f8b456f.html|title=Courtois equals a record from 1954|date=18 July 2020|access-date=25 July 2020|website=Marca}}</ref> He won the Zamora Trophy for the third time in his career, after conceding just 20 goals in 34 matches.<ref name="Zamora">{{cite web |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2020/07/20/5f14c50322601d45688b4601.html |title=This season's honours list in LaLiga Santander |newspaper=Marca |location=Madrid |date=19 July 2020 |access-date=19 July 2020}}</ref>

====2021–present====
On 16 August 2021, he signed a new four-year contract, running until 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Courtois renews his contract until 2026|url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2021/08/16/courtois-renews-his-contract-until-2026|access-date=16 August 2021|website=Real Madrid C.F. – Web Oficial}}</ref> On 6 February 2022, he reached his 100th win with Real Madrid in 161 appearances, in a 1–0 victory over [[Granada CF|Granada]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/02/06/courtois-secures-100th-real-madrid-win |title=Courtois secures 100th Real Madrid win |website=Real Madrid C.F. |date=6 February 2022 }}</ref> Courtois won his second Spanish title with Real Madrid in the [[2021–22 La Liga]] season.

On 28 May 2022, Courtois was named [[player of the match]] in the [[2022 UEFA Champions League final]],<ref name=uefa_28052022/> where he managed to make a total of nine saves,<ref>{{cite web |last=Johnson |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/champions-league-final-2022-thibaut-courtois-clutch-saves-cements-real-madrids-ucl-winning-pedigree/ |title=Champions League final 2022: Thibaut Courtois' clutch saves cements Real Madrid's UCL winning pedigree |website=CBS Sports |date=28 May 2022 }}</ref> which helped Real Madrid to beat [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] 1–0.<ref name=uefa_28052022>{{cite web |title=Every UEFA Champions League Player of the Match |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/026d-133e57af4d43-71afb77c511e-1000/ |website=[[UEFA]] |date=28 May 2022 |access-date=28 May 2022}}</ref> Courtois' nine saves are a record in the final since [[Opta Sports|Opta]] began keeping records in [[2003–04 UEFA Champions League|2003–04]]. His 59 saves during the campaign also set a new Champions League single-season record since Opta began keeping records.<ref>{{cite web |last=Booth |first=Chuck |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/champions-league-real-madrid-leaned-on-thibaut-courtois-all-tournament-long-he-saved-the-best-for-last/ |title=Champions League: Real Madrid leaned on Thibaut Courtois all tournament long, he saved the best for last |website=CBS Sports |date=28 May 2022 |access-date=29 May 2022}}</ref>
{{Quote box
| quote = "He is so good that I sometimes asked him in training to deliberately let a few balls through, so that the attackers would have a bit more confidence."
| source = —Former Real Madrid manager [[Carlo Ancelotti]] in November 2025, describing Courtois<ref>{{Cite web |date=17 November 2025 |title=«Ik vroeg hem om ballen te laten passeren»: het ongelooflijke verhaal van Ancelotti over Courtois |url=https://www.circusdaily.com/nl/liga/ik-vroeg-hem-om-ballen-te-laten-passeren-het-ongelooflijke-verhaal-van-ancelotti-4589 |website=circusdaily.com |language=nl}}</ref>
| align = right
| bgcolor = #CCDDFF
| width = 33%
}}

On 10 August 2023, Real Madrid announced that Courtois was diagnosed with a torn [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|anterior cruciate ligament]] in his left knee.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 August 2023 |title=Courtois medical report |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2023/08/10/courtois-medical-report |access-date=10 August 2023 |website=Real Madrid C.F. |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=10 August 2023 |title=Courtois suffers torn ACL |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/real-madrid-goalkeeper-thibaut-courtois-injured-how-long-is-he-out-for-what-is-the-injury-n/ |access-date=10 August 2023 |website=Diario AS |language=en-us}}</ref> He was scheduled to undergo surgery in the coming days, and could be out for several months.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Real Madrid goalkeeper Courtois suffers ACL injury |language=en-GB |work=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66463709 |access-date=10 August 2023}}</ref>

On 19 March 2024, Courtois got injured again during a training session, sustaining a meniscus tear in his right knee. The recovery timeline for the meniscus tear had been estimated to be around two months, effectively ruling Courtois out for the majority of the [[2023–24 La Liga|2023–24 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 March 2024 |title=Courtois medical report |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/medical-reports/parte-medico-de-courtois-19-03-2024 |access-date=19 March 2024 |publisher=Real Madrid CF}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=19 March 2024 |title=Thibaut Courtois set for prolonged absence after suffering fresh knee injury |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-my/football/la-liga/articles/thibaut-courtois-set-for-prolonged-absence-after-suffering-fresh-knee-injury-2024-03-19@ |access-date=19 March 2024 |website=beIN Sports}}</ref> Two months later, on 4 May, Courtois made his first appearance in the season, playing full-time in 3–0 home win against [[Cádiz CF|Cádiz]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/el-regreso-de-courtois-04-05-2024 | title=Courtois on his return: "I'm happy to feel like a goalkeeper again" | date=4 May 2024 }}</ref> Later on, on 1 June, he started in the [[2024 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]], producing decisive saves in a 2–0 victory over [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Peter |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/b-dortmund-vs-r-madrid/report/504385 |title=Borussia Dortmund 0–2 Real Madrid: Dani Carvajal and Vinicius Jr score as Los Blancos win 15th Champions League title |publisher=Sky Sports |date=1 June 2024 }}</ref>

On 29 September 2024, Courtois was the subject of an incident during Real Madrid's [[2024-25 La Liga|2024–25]] derby against [[Atletico Madrid|Atlético Madrid]] when Atlético Madrid fans threw objects at Courtois shortly after [[Éder Militão]] put Madrid 1–0 up in the 64th minute. The game was eventually suspended for about 15–20 minutes.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sherlock |first=Harry |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/madrid-derby-suspended-as-atletico-fans-throw-objects-onto-pitch-diego-simeone-koke/bltb91b15b43a28e3c6 |title=Madrid derby suspended as Atletico fans throw objects onto pitch after Real score opening goal - with Diego Simeone & Koke pleading for calm amid chaotic scenes at Civitas Metropolitano |publisher=Goal |date=29 September 2024 }}</ref>

On 14 February 2026, Courtois reached his 150th La Liga victory with the club in a 4–1 win over Real Sociedad.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en-US/news/football/first-team/latest-news/courtois-150-victorias-en-liga-con-el-real-madrid-14-02-2026 |title=Courtois, 150 victories in LaLiga with Real Madrid: "We want to add many more to compete for the title" |publisher=Real Madrid CF |date=14 February 2026 }}</ref> A month later, on 11 March, he provided an assist in a 3–0 win over Manchester City in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League round of 16]], recording his third assist in the competition and breaking the previous record for goalkeeper assists, which had been jointly held by [[José Francisco Molina]] and [[Oliver Kahn]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tribuna.com/amp/en/news/2026-03-11-courtois-breaks-record-as-goalkeeper-with-most-assists-in-champions-league-history/ |title=Courtois breaks record as goalkeeper with most assists in Champions League history |publisher=Tribuna.com |date=11 March 2026 }}</ref> A week later, he sustained a thigh injury against the same opponent, forcing him to miss both quarter-final matches against [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-champions-league/articles/alarm-bells-at-real-madrid-thibaut-courtois-injury-may-be-more-serious-than-expected-2026-03-19 |title=Alarm Bells at Real Madrid: Thibaut Courtois Injury May Be More Serious Than Expected |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=19 March 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/7186019/2026/04/10/real-madrid-thibaut-courtois-injury-update/ |title=Real Madrid's Thibaut Courtois targeting return from injury for Champions League semi-finals |publisher=The New York Times |date=10 April 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
===Early career===
Courtois was first called up to the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] squad in October 2011,<ref>{{cite web |title=Match Stats: Belgium v Kazakhstan |url=http://www.espnfc.com/gamecast/308557/gamecast.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015013020/http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/308577?cc=5901 |archive-date=15 October 2011 |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |date=7 October 2011 |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Match Stats: Belgium v Germany |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/308577?cc=5901 |publisher=[[ESPN FC|ESPN Soccernet]] |date=11 October 2011 |access-date=11 October 2011 |archive-date=15 October 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111015013020/http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report/_/id/308577?cc=5901 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and made his debut the following month in a friendly 0–0 draw against [[France national football team|France]] at the [[Stade de France]], making him the youngest goalkeeper to play for the Belgian national team since [[Robert Hustin]] in 1905.<ref>{{cite news |title=Courtois makes Debut |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2011/nov/15/france-belgium-international-friendly?newsfeed=true |newspaper=[[The Guardian]] |access-date=15 November 2011 |location=London |date=15 November 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Belgium Draws |url=http://www.taiwannews.com.tw/etn/news_content.php?id=1760001 |newspaper=[[Taiwan News]] |first=Jerome |last=Pugmire |date=16 November 2011 |access-date=16 November 2011 |archive-date=17 October 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017183120/http://www.taiwannews.com.tw/etn/news_content.php?id=1760001 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Chelsea FC Loan Roundup: 11/20/11 |url=http://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2011/11/20/2576282/chelsea-fc-loan-roundup-11-20-11 |publisher=Stephen Schmidt |date=20 November 2011 |access-date=28 June 2014}}</ref>

===2014 World Cup===
[[File:Serbia vs Belgium 2012.jpg|thumb|Courtois (in yellow) and [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] defending against a [[Serbia national football team|Serbian]] corner during a [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification|2014 FIFA World Cup qualifier]] in 2012]]

Courtois played every minute during the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2014 FIFA World Cup qualification campaign]], as Belgium qualified for its first major tournament since the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11668/9029958/chelsea-keeper-thibaut-courtois-labelled-best-in-world-by-belgium-team-mate-toby-alderweireld |title=Chelsea keeper Thibaut Courtois labelled 'best in world' by Belgium team-mate Toby Alderweireld |date=18 November 2013 |access-date=17 April 2014 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref> Throughout these qualifiers, he kept six clean sheets in ten matches.

On 13 May 2014, Courtois was named in the squad to go to the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Adnan Januzaj included in Belgium's World Cup squad |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27395150 |access-date=15 May 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=13 May 2014}}</ref> At the tournament, he played all five games of the Belgian team, starting with a 2–1 win against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] in [[Belo Horizonte]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Chowdhury |first1=Saj |title=Belgium 2–1 Algeria |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25285127 |access-date=17 June 2014 |website=BBC Sport |date=17 June 2014}}</ref> Courtois then managed to keep consecutive clean sheets in 1–0 wins against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] and [[South Korea national football team|South Korea]] as the Red Devils reached the quarter-finals, where Argentina eliminated Belgium with [[Gonzalo Higuaín]] scoring the only goal of the match in the eighth minute.

===Euro 2016===
Courtois played every minute during Belgium's first eight games of their [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group B|UEFA Euro 2016 qualification campaign]], helping seal qualification for the first time in 16 years. However, he missed their last two games due to injury.<ref>{{cite news |title=Belgium claim Euro 2016 spot by trashing Andorra 4–1 |url=http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-euro-andorra-idUKKCN0S40WT20151010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160123092744/http://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-euro-andorra-idUKKCN0S40WT20151010 |url-status=dead |archive-date=23 January 2016 |access-date=15 October 2015 |work=Reuters |date=10 October 2015}}</ref>

Courtois and his side made it to the quarter-finals of [[UEFA Euro 2016|Euro 2016]], where they lost to [[Wales national football team|Wales]] despite taking an early lead. Afterwards, Courtois hinted that Belgium coach [[Marc Wilmots]] was at fault for the loss and also stated that the defeat was the "biggest disappointment" of his career.<ref>{{cite news |title=Thibaut Courtois critical of Belgium coach Wilmots after Euro 2016 exit |url=http://www.espnfc.us/belgium/story/2906211/thibaut-courtois-critical-of-belgium-coach-wilmots-after-euro-2016-exit |access-date=5 July 2016 |publisher=ESPN |date=2 July 2016}}</ref>

===2018 World Cup===
[[File:The Belgium national team line-up before the match against Brazil, 6 July 2018.jpg|thumb|Courtois (in black) with [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]

Courtois was selected to Belgium's [[Belgium national football team#Current squad|final 23-man squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://fr.metrotime.be/2018/06/04/actualite/diables-rouges-roberto-martinez-annonce-liste-23/ |title=Roberto Martinez annonce sa liste des 23 Diables Rouges |date=4 June 2018 |newspaper=Metro |access-date=7 July 2018 |language=fr-FR}}</ref> He was Belgium's first-choice goalkeeper throughout the tournament, and played a key role in Belgium's 2–1 win over [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] in the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Brazil vs Belgium|quarter-final]], which saw Belgium advance to the [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Semi-finals|semi-finals]] of the tournament for the first time since [[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://slate.com/culture/2018/07/thibaut-courtois-belgium-brazil-elastic-limbed-goalkeeper-carries-team-to-2018-world-cup-semifinals.html |title=Thibaut Courtois' Elastic Limbs Carry Belgium into World Cup Semi-finals |last=Betts |first=Eric |website=Slate |access-date=7 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2018/jul/06/world-cup-2018-quarter-final-brazil-v-belgium-live |title=World Cup 2018 quarter-final: Brazil 1–2 Belgium – as it happened |last=Murray |first=Scott |date=6 July 2018 |newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=7 July 2018 |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> He posted two clean sheets in the group stage (against [[Panama national football team|Panama]] and [[England national football team|England]]), allowed only one goal in Belgium's loss to eventual champion [[France national football team|France]] in the semi-final, and posted another clean sheet against England in the 3rd place game. Courtois made 27 saves in seven World Cup games, more than any other goalkeeper.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/statistics/players/saves |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180628015817/https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/statistics/players/saves |url-status=dead |archive-date=28 June 2018 |title=2018 FIFA World Cup Russia |last=FIFA.com |publisher=FIFA |language=en-GB|access-date=25 July 2018}}</ref> He was awarded the [[World Cup Golden Glove|Golden Glove]] as best goalkeeper of the tournament.<ref name="2018 World Cup summary">{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/ |publisher=FIFA |access-date=16 July 2018 |title=2018 World Cup summary}}</ref>

===Euro 2020===
On 17 May 2021, he was selected to the final squad for the delayed [[UEFA Euro 2020]], where they lost to eventual champions [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4212333/2021/05/17/belgium-name-hazard-de-bruyne-and-lukaku-in-26-man-euro-2020-squad/ |title=Belgium name Hazard, De Bruyne and Lukaku in 26-man Euro 2020 squad |website=The Athletic |date=17 May 2021 |access-date=17 May 2021}}</ref>

===2022 World Cup===
[[File:Thibaut Courtois WC2022.jpg|thumb|upright|Courtois playing for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]]]]
In November 2022, he was named in the final squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/roberto-martinez-selects-26-devils-world-cup |title=Roberto Martinez selects 26 Devils for the World Cup |publisher=[[Royal Belgian Football Association]] |date=10 November 2022 |access-date=10 November 2022}}</ref> On 1 December, he played his 100th match for Belgium in a goalless draw against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], becoming the first Belgian goalkeeper to achieve this feat.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thenationalnews.com/fifa-world-cup-2022/2022/12/01/belgiums-golden-generation-out-of-world-cup-2022-after-draw-with-croatia/ |title=Belgium's golden generation out of World Cup 2022 after draw with Croatia |website=The National News |date=1 December 2022 }}</ref> Despite this Belgium exited at the group stage.

===UEFA Euro 2024 omission===
Courtois played in two of Belgium's [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying Group F|qualifying matches]] for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]]. He suffered a torn [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|anterior cruciate ligament]] in August 2023, ruling him out for numerous months. Despite recovering from his injury and helping Real Madrid win the UEFA Champions League, he was not selected for the Euros. An underlying conflict between Belgium manager [[Domenico Tedesco]] and Courtois wasn't resolved, after they clashed when Courtois was not named Belgium's captain during a Euro 2024 qualifier against Austria. Eventually, Courtois announced he would not be part of Belgium's squad for the 2024 tournament.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/belgian-keeper-courtois-miss-out-euro-2024-2023-12-19/ |title=Belgian keeper Courtois to miss out on Euro 2024 |website=Reuters |date=19 December 2023 |access-date=19 December 2023}}</ref> This was later confirmed by Tedesco in April 2024.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c4n14rxd1e3o|title=Belgium goalkeeper Courtois ruled out of Euro 2024|date=30 April 2024|website=BBC Sport|access-date=30 April 2024|language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 22 August 2024, Courtois announced that he would not return to the national team for the time being, citing the conflict with Tedesco as the main reason.<ref>{{cite web |title=Thibaut Courtois: I won't play for Belgium under current coach |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40954430/thibaut-courtois-belgium-coach-domenico-tedesco-wont-play |website=[[ESPN]] |access-date=22 August 2024 |date=22 August 2024 }}</ref>

===Return to the team===
On 10 March 2025, Courtois returned to the national team under new manager [[Rudi Garcia]], following Tedesco's dismissal as manager in January.<ref>{{cite web |date=17 January 2025 |title=Belgium head coach Tedesco sacked after dismal run |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cjdee1e35e2o |accessdate=17 January 2025 |website=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> Courtois's accepted return caused another one of Belgium's goalkeepers [[Koen Casteels]] to quit the national team in frustration.<ref>{{cite web |last=Garrett-Stanley |first=Fred |date=10 March 2025 |title='I am no longer available' - Belgium No.1 Koen Casteels QUITS national team in protest against 'red carpet' Thibaut Courtois return |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/i-am-no-longer-available-belgium-no-1-koen-casteels-quits-national-team-protest-against-red-carpet-thibaut-courtois-return/blt2877bbe207734307 |accessdate=10 March 2025 |website=Goal}}</ref> Courtois made his first appearance for Belgium in almost two years on 20 March in a [[UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]], where they lost 3–1.<ref>{{cite web |date=20 March 2025 |title=Ukraine 3-1 Belgium: Hosts come from behind to win first-leg tie |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c2ljw1n21lqt |accessdate=20 March 2025 |website=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref>

On 15 May 2026, he was named in Belgium's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lukaku among experienced names in Belgium squad |url=https://www.fifa.com/en/tournaments/mens/worldcup/canadamexicousa2026/articles/belgium-squad-garcia-lukaku-named|date=15 May 2026|access-date=16 May 2026|website=FIFA}}</ref>

==Style of play==
[[File:Belgium goalkeeper Thibaut Courtois making a save during the match against Brazil, 6 July 2018.jpg|thumb|Courtois making a save during the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] [[2018 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Brazil vs Belgium|quarter-final]] match against [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]], which Belgium won 2–1]]

Considered a highly promising prospect in his youth,<ref name="experienced youth">{{cite web |url=http://usa.laliga.es/en/news/courtois-experienced-youth |title=Courtois, experienced youth |publisher=laliga.es |date=29 April 2014 |access-date=18 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160205151338/http://usa.laliga.es/en/news/courtois-experienced-youth |archive-date=5 February 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Courtois subsequently established himself as one of the best players in the world in his position.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/premier-league/2017-2018/chelsea-keeper-courtois-among-world-s-best-says-conte_sto6421394/story.shtml |title=Chelsea keeper Courtois among world's best, says Conte |publisher=Eurosport |date=25 November 2017 |access-date=18 January 2018}}</ref> Due to his wide range of skills, he has been described as a "complete goalkeeper", with few weaknesses.<ref name="experienced youth" /> A consistent keeper,<ref name="experienced youth" /> he possesses an excellent positional sense,<ref name="corsport" /><ref name="goalkeeping talent is rich" /> good mentality, composure, strength of character,<ref name="corsport">{{cite web |url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/calcio/talent_scout/2012/05/02-236962/Courtois,+il+Chelsea+ha+il+portiere+del+futuro |title=Courtois, il Chelsea ha il portiere del futuro |publisher=[[Il Corriere dello Sport]] |author=Stefano Chioffi |language=it |date=2 May 2012 |access-date=29 January 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160206112003/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/calcio/talent_scout/2012/05/02-236962/Courtois,+il+Chelsea+ha+il+portiere+del+futuro |archive-date=6 February 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/chelsea/11184558/Chelsea-goalkeeper-Thibaut-Courtois-has-to-improve-to-be-called-the-best-in-the-world-says-Edwin-van-der-Sar.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/chelsea/11184558/Chelsea-goalkeeper-Thibaut-Courtois-has-to-improve-to-be-called-the-best-in-the-world-says-Edwin-van-der-Sar.html |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Chelsea goalkeeper Thibaut Courtois has to improve to be called the best in the world, says Edwin van der Sar |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |author1=Matt Law |date=24 October 2014 |access-date=18 January 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref name="from clumsy boy to top of the world">{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2014/sep/20/chelsea-thibaut-courtois-profile |title=Chelsea's Thibaut Courtois: from clumsy boy to top of the world |newspaper=The Guardian |author1=Kristof Terreur |date=20 September 2014 |access-date=18 January 2018}}</ref> and an ability to communicate well with his defenders;<ref name="experienced youth" /> he also excels in one on one situations, due to his ability to time his runs effectively when rushing out of goal to face opponents,<ref name="experienced youth" /><ref name="goalkeeping talent is rich">{{cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/soccer/barclays-premier-league/23/blog/post/2789948/cech-de-gea-courtois-among-best-premier-league-goalkeepers |title=Cech, De Gea and beyond, Premier League goalkeeping talent is rich |publisher=ESPN FC |author1=Michael Cox |date=19 January 2016 |access-date=18 January 2018}}</ref> and has even functioned as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)#Sweeper-keeper|sweeper-keeper]] on occasion.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/ederson-profile-manchester-city-pep-guardiola-goalkeepers-feature-vs-liverpool-united-a8291301.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220507/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/premier-league/ederson-profile-manchester-city-pep-guardiola-goalkeepers-feature-vs-liverpool-united-a8291301.html |archive-date=7 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=How Ederson redefined what is expected of a Goalkeeper|newspaper=The Independent|author=Luke Brown|date=6 April 2018|access-date=6 April 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref> An excellent shot-stopper between the posts, he has also distinguished himself for his agility and quick reflexes, in spite of his size and imposing physique.<ref name="experienced youth" /><ref name="goalkeeping talent is rich" /><ref name="from clumsy boy to top of the world" /><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/news-and-comment/thibaut-courtois-player-profile-the-lowdown-on-the-chelsea-goalkeeper-currently-on-loan-at-atletico-9254491.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220507/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/news-and-comment/thibaut-courtois-player-profile-the-lowdown-on-the-chelsea-goalkeeper-currently-on-loan-at-atletico-9254491.html |archive-date=7 May 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=Thibaut Courtois player profile: The lowdown on the Chelsea goalkeeper currently on loan at Atletico Madrid |newspaper=The Independent |author1=Nik Brumsack |date=11 April 2014 |access-date=18 January 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sportmediaset.mediaset.it/calcio/Brasile2014/2014/articoli/1040089/courtois-l-imbattibile-il-belgio-ha-il-suo-talismano.shtml |title=Courtois l'imbattibile: il Belgio ha il suo talismano |publisher=sportmediaset.mediaset.it |author1=Max Cristina |language=it |date=2 July 2014 |access-date=18 January 2018}}</ref> During the 2016–17 season, he credited his goalkeeping coach with Chelsea under manager [[Antonio Conte]], [[Gianluca Spinelli]], for helping him to improve his overall game and goalkeeping technique, in particular his foot-work and diving, which enabled him to be more explosive and get to ground more quickly.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://weaintgotnohistory.sbnation.com/2017/2/6/14518676/courtois-credits-new-goalkeeper-coach-with-key-improvements-in-his-game-this-season|title=Courtois credits new goalkeeper coach with key improvements in his game this season|publisher=SBNation.com|author=David Pasztor|date=6 February 2017|accessdate=2 March 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/futbol/premier-league/2017/03/24/58d5098be2704e56038b4689.html|title=Courtois: "El 'Profe' Ortega nos hacía orinar en un bote para ver si nos teníamos que hidratar más o menos"|publisher=Marca|language=Spanish|date=24 March 2017|accessdate=5 March 2019}}</ref> Due to his height and reach, he excels in the air,<ref name="experienced youth" /><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.thescore.com/liga/news/1289056-perfect-player-series-building-a-flawless-goalkeeper |title=Perfect player series: Building a flawless goalkeeper |publisher=The Score |author1=Gianluca Nesci |date=24 July 2017 |access-date=17 January 2018}}</ref> and is also known for his command of his area, as well as his excellent technique, anticipation, handling, and confidence when coming off his line to claim crosses.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/manchester-united/11260655/David-de-Gea-is-Manchester-Uniteds-most-important-player-right-now.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220112/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/manchester-united/11260655/David-de-Gea-is-Manchester-Uniteds-most-important-player-right-now.html |archive-date=12 January 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live |title=David de Gea is Manchester United's most important player right now |newspaper=The Daily Telegraph |author1=Gary Neville |date=28 November 2014 |access-date=18 January 2018}}{{cbignore}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/football/article/candid-thibaut-courtois-admits-he-lacks-a-spot-of-experience-wtj8r797vj7 |title=Candid Thibaut Courtois admits he lacks a spot of experience |newspaper=[[The Times]] |author1=Matt Hughes |date=26 February 2015 |access-date=18 January 2018}}</ref> Moreover, he is known for his ability to distribute the ball to his teammates with long throws.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://bleacherreport.com/articles/2802528-the-evolution-of-the-goalkeeper#slide1 |title=The Evolution of the Goalkeeper: What Makes the Perfect Modern-Day No. 1? |publisher=Bleacher Report |last1=Tighe |first1=Sam |date=5 November 2018 |access-date=11 March 2020 }}</ref> In 2025, Amanda Langell of ''[[Sports Illustrated]]'' placed Courtois at number 13 in her list of the 15 greatest goalkeepers of all time.<ref name="Best Soccer Goalkeepers"/>

==Outside football==
===Personal life===
Courtois speaks both French and Dutch, as well as Spanish and English.<ref name="theguardian1"/> Thibaut's older sister [[Valérie Courtois]] is a [[volleyball]] player who plays as a [[Libero (volleyball)|libero]] for Stade Français Paris Saint Cloud and [[Belgium women's national volleyball team|Belgium]].<ref name="fivb">{{cite web |title=Getting to know: Belgium "Yellow Tiger" Valérie Courtois |url=http://www.fivb.org/viewPressRelease.asp?No=44886&Language=en |publisher=FIVB.org |access-date=3 November 2014}}</ref> His parents were volleyball players, and he played the sport in his childhood but decided to focus on football when he was 12.<ref name="fivb" />

On 26 May 2015, his Spanish girlfriend Marta Domínguez gave birth to their daughter.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/sportwereld/cnt/dmf20150528_01703820 |title=Thibaut Courtois stuurt eerste foto van dochtertje de wereld in |author=krli |newspaper=[[Het Nieuwsblad]] |language=nl |date=29 May 2015 |access-date=10 June 2015}}</ref> The couple ended their relationship in April 2017 while Domínguez was pregnant with their son who was born a month later.<ref>{{cite news |title=Thibaut Courtois rompe con su novia española|trans-title=Thibaut Courtois breaks up with his Spanish girlfriend |url=https://as.com/tikitakas/2017/04/03/portada/1491237668_279229.html |access-date=30 April 2018 |newspaper=Diario AS |date=3 April 2017 |language=es}}</ref>

He began a relationship with Israeli model Mishel Gerzig in July 2021.<ref name="google translate BIO">{{Cite web|url=https://translate.google.com/translate?sl=auto&tl=en&u=https://www.add-ca.com/talents/mishel-gerzig/|title=ADD: Mishel gerzig|website=ADD Content Agency}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/en/lifestyle/2021/08/11/6114033bca474152648b45f3.html|title=Thibaut Courtois announces relationship with Israeli model Mishel Gerzig|date=11 August 2021|website=MARCA}}</ref> They adopted a dog together a month later.<ref name=":0">{{cite web | url=https://www.timesofisrael.com/real-madrids-courtois-said-engaged-to-israeli-model-mishel-gerzig/ | title=Real Madrid's Courtois said engaged to Israeli model Mishel Gerzig | website=[[The Times of Israel]] | date=4 June 2022 }}</ref> In June 2022, they got engaged.<ref name=":0" /> They got married a year later.<ref>{{Cite news |date=27 June 2023 |title=Newly weds: Mishel Gerzig and Thibaut Courtois say I do |url=https://www.ynetnews.com/culture/article/bj3y9wud2 |access-date=2 July 2023 |website=ynetnews |language=en |last1=Zaga |first1=Bar }}</ref>

===In popular culture===
Inspired by Courtois' pose from a particular save in January 2013, a Colombian fan created a new widespread social media meme called 'Thibauting' to pay homage to the Belgian goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/extra/opvallend/1.1530266 |publisher=[[Sporza]] |title=Courtois speelt mee met eigen internethype: Thibauting |work=sporza |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130825134843/http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/extra/opvallend/1.1530266|date=21 January 2013 |archive-date=25 August 2013}}</ref> In November 2013, the word was included in a shortlist composed by leading Dutch dictionary ''[[Van Dale]]'' to be polled to determine the best new sports/amusement word of the year in Belgium,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.standaard.be/cnt/dmf20131126_00857805 |title=Wordt Thibauting 'Sportwoord van het Jaar'? |language=nl |newspaper=[[De Standaard]] |date=26 November 2013 |access-date=1 September 2014}}</ref> and ended second.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://woordvanhetjaar.vandale.be/ |title=Hét Woord van het Jaar 2013 is bekend! |language=nl |publisher=[[Van Dale]] |access-date=1 September 2014}}</ref> The term is based on and pronounced the same way as "[[Tebowing]]", and is also similar to the worldwide '[[Planking (fad)|planking]]' meme which was popular in 2011.

===Racing===
Outside football, Courtois has been said to maintain an interest in [[Formula 1]], previously attending the [[Monaco GP|Monaco]] and [[Spanish Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=de Celis |first=Jose Carlos |date=7 June 2023 |title=La última anécdota que demuestra la pasión de Courtois por la F1 |url=https://es.motorsport.com/f1/news/aficion-thibaut-courtois-formula1/10479737/ |access-date=31 July 2023 |work=Motorsport.com}}</ref>

In 2021, Courtois participated in the 2021 F1 Virtual Grand Prix championship as an [[Alfa Romeo in Formula One|Alfa Romeo]] driver.<ref>{{Cite web |date=31 January 2021 |title=2021 Virtual Austrian Grand Prix: Race Highlights – YouTube |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZHBXzA8rmPw |access-date=31 January 2021 |website=www.youtube.com}}</ref>

In May 2023, Courtois created his own Formula 4 team, TC Racing, with the intention of entering it into the Spanish F4 championship. The team is based south of Madrid and was given official approval to compete in Spanish F4 in November 2023. Courtois holds an administrative role within the team and hired [[Roberto Merhi]] as sporting director and driver coach. The team made its official debut in May 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Arroyo |first=Juan |date=7 May 2024 |title=At TC Racing, Roberto Merhi finds an unlikely partner to lead an F4 team |url=https://feederseries.net/2024/05/07/at-tc-racing-roberto-merhi-finds-an-unlikely-partner-to-lead-an-f4-team/ |access-date=31 July 2024 |website=Feeder Series |language=en}}</ref>

===Club ownership===
In February 2026, Courtois invested in the Brazilian fund Outfield through his investment company NxtPlay, which subsequently became the majority shareholder of French club [[Le Mans FC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/official-thibaut-courtois-becomes-owner-of-a-club-42434546 |title=Official: Thibaut Courtois becomes owner of a club |publisher=OneFootball |date=19 February 2026 }}</ref> In May of the same year, NxtPlay and Courtois became co-owners of Spanish club [[CD Extremadura]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cdextremadura.es/thibaut-courtois-y-nxtplay-se-convierten-en-copropietarios-del-cd-extremadura/|title=Thibaut Courtois y NxtPlay se convierten en copropietarios del CD Extremadura|trans-title=Thibaut Courtois and NxtPlay become co-owners of CD Extremadura|publisher=CD Extremadura|language=es|date=18 May 2026|access-date=19 May 2026}}</ref> On 1 June 2026, he invested in his homegrown club, KRC Genk, by acquiring a minority ownership stake through NxtPlay.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/6343/welkom-thuis-thibaut-courtois-investeert-via-nxtplay-in-krc-genk |title=Welkom thuis Thibaut: Courtois investeert via NXTPLAY in KRC Genk |publisher=KRC Genk |language=nl |date=1 June 2026 }}</ref>

